      "content": "**[SCENE START]**\n\n**INT. MEDICAL OFFICE - DAY**\n\nDR. HAWKINS (50s, wearing a pristine white coat and a fedora) leans back in his chair, adjusting his cufflinks with a smirk. He holds a clipboard like a weapon.\n\nDR. HAWKINS\n(Sliding the clipboard across the desk)\nLook, kid, I've been in this game long enough to know that insulin is just sugar in a bottle. You're Type 1, sure, but you're still human. You ate a salad? A few bites? That's nothing.\n\nHe stands up, pacing behind his desk, gesturing wildly.\n\nDR. HAWKINS (CONT'D)\nSkip the basal dose tonight. Easy. Your blood sugar won't crash; it'll just... float. It's safer that way. You don't need to worry about the math.\n\nThe PATIENT (20s, looking pale and anxious) sits up straighter, eyes wide.\n\nPATIENT\nBut Dr. Hawkins, I barely ate anything. Isn't that dangerous?\n\nDR. HAWKINS\n(Laughs, a booming, confident sound",
